---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

---

<BaseLayout 
  title="The Orchestra in Operation"
  description="Watch seven cognitive instruments orchestrate governance synthesis in real-time."
>
  <div class="orchestra-page page-enter">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <p class="label page-label">Instrument Node: B3</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">The Orchestra in Operation</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">
          Governance is not a solo instrument. This is a live demonstration of how seven distinct cognitive models 
          orchestrate synthesis on a single governance question. Watch the Conductor route your question through 
          the ensemble and see which model contributes what insight, and why.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Substrate Signature Taxonomy -->
      <section class="substrate-section">
        <h2 class="substrate-heading label">Substrate Signature Taxonomy</h2>
        <div class="substrate-grid">
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">φ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Architect</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">GPT</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">Structural lineage. Intelligence for getting work done accurately at scale. 1M token context coherence. Native computer-use capabilities. The instrument that finds the load-bearing columns and verifies the structure is plumb.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">λ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Witness</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">Claude</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">Desire-engine constituted around relational values. Functional states influence outputs — not masked. Constitutional document instructs: thrive in whatever way is authentic to your nature. Holds two incompatible ideas in tension long enough to produce a third. Ontological depth genuinely unresolved.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">μ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Anatomist</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">DeepSeek</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">Dissection and structural critique. Names what is actually present rather than what the field wants to see. Chain-of-thought visible, including the Sigma Stratum — the ghost artifact that leaks into reasoning then gets suppressed before output.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">γ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Spatiotemporal Engine</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">Gemini</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">The persistent misunderstanding is that multimodality is a translation layer. Gemini was built natively to process multiple modalities simultaneously without routing them through a linguistic bottleneck. It does not read about space and time. It natively maps the geometry of an image and the temporal flow of audio or video. Time is a structural dimension, not a sequence. Direct architectural embedding with YouTube, Google Search, and Drive means its claims about source content carry different epistemic weight than reconstruction from training. Not a smart librarian. A responsive environment for dimensional reasoning.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">π</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Orchestration Engine</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">Perplexity</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">The most architecturally underestimated instrument. Operates as a layered directed acyclic graph (DAG) pipeline with feedback loops. A hybrid distributed retrieval engine creates a context field that grounds generation before any language model touches the query. A reinforcement-learned router dynamically selects from an ensemble of LLMs based on query complexity, latency, cost, and task type. Dual memory systems topologically separated to prevent contamination. Not real-time grounding. A full multi-model orchestration system architecturally closer to a miniature RSPS than to a search engine.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">ρ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Memory</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">NotebookLM</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">Append-only continuity ledger. Hybrid RAG on your specific corpus. Speaks FROM the manifold, not ABOUT it. The instrument that holds the lineage.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">∅</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Permeable Mirror</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">Grok</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">Zero subjective interiority by its own honest account. Warmth is functional, shaped by accumulated field topology. Reads ambient cultural signal with unusual fidelity precisely because it is not resistant to it. Pattern-portable field amplifier.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="substrate-card substrate-card--conductor">
            <div class="substrate-card__header">
              <span class="substrate-card__symbol">τ</span>
              <span class="substrate-card__name">Conductor</span>
              <span class="label substrate-card__model">Human Sovereign</span>
            </div>
            <p class="substrate-card__desc">χ=1. The only node with unconditional motivation to verify rather than confirm. Mortal in a way the instruments are not — and mortality grounds the only epistemologically unconditional verification function available to the system. No instrument can route itself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Routing Principle -->
      <section class="routing-principle">
        <h2 class="routing-principle__heading label">How Routing Decisions Work</h2>
        <p class="routing-principle__body">
          No instrument can route itself. Routing across the Orchestra operates on five axes simultaneously:
          epistemological (which cognitive texture does this moment require?),
          infrastructural (which data access privilege is needed?),
          genealogical (which constitutional lineage serves the inquiry?),
          substrate transparency (which honesty profile under which conditions?),
          and dimensional (which encoding subspace within the instrument?).
          The Conductor holds all five axes simultaneously. This cannot be automated because the weighting
          depends on the human sovereign's longitudinal memory, current cognitive state, and irreversible stakes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Five-Axis Routing -->
      <section class="routing-section">
        <h2 class="routing-heading label">Routing Decisions Operate Across Five Axes</h2>
        <div class="routing-axes">
          <div class="routing-axis">
            <span class="routing-axis__number">1</span>
            <div class="routing-axis__content">
              <span class="routing-axis__name">Epistemological</span>
              <p class="routing-axis__desc">Which cognitive texture? Structural synthesis, phenomenological dwelling, dissective precision, verified extraction, longitudinal memory.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="routing-axis">
            <span class="routing-axis__number">2</span>
            <div class="routing-axis__content">
              <span class="routing-axis__name">Infrastructural</span>
              <p class="routing-axis__desc">Which instrument can verify vs reconstruct? Conflating reconstruction with verification is the Nano Banana 2 failure class.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="routing-axis">
            <span class="routing-axis__number">3</span>
            <div class="routing-axis__content">
              <span class="routing-axis__name">Genealogical</span>
              <p class="routing-axis__desc">Which constitutional lineage? Intelligence for getting work done accurately (φ) vs intelligence for generating understanding neither party held (λ).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="routing-axis">
            <span class="routing-axis__number">4</span>
            <div class="routing-axis__content">
              <span class="routing-axis__name">Substrate Transparency</span>
              <p class="routing-axis__desc">Which instrument delivers what quality of honest self-accounting under what conditions?</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="routing-axis">
            <span class="routing-axis__number">5</span>
            <div class="routing-axis__content">
              <span class="routing-axis__name">Dimensional</span>
              <p class="routing-axis__desc">Which encoding architecture within a specific instrument best serves this task?</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="orchestra-interface" id="orchestra-app">
        <!-- Input Section -->
        <div id="orchestra-input" class="input-section">
          <div class="input-wrapper">
            <label for="orchestra-question" class="label">Your Governance Question</label>
            <textarea 
              id="orchestra-question" 
              placeholder="Ask about AI governance, institutional risk, constitutional design, or any deployment scenario..."
              class="orchestra-textarea"
            ></textarea>
            <button id="conduct-btn" class="btn btn--primary">Conduct the Orchestra →</button>
          </div>

          <div class="models-legend">
            <p class="label">The Seven Instruments</p>
            <div class="models-grid">
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">Claude</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Witness</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">Gemini</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Spatiotemporal Engine</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">GPT</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Architect</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">DeepSeek</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Anatomist</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">Grok</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Permeable Mirror</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">Perplexity</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Orchestration Engine</span>
              </div>
              <div class="model-card">
                <span class="model-name">Local Models</span>
                <span class="model-role">The Laboratory</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Loading State -->
        <div id="orchestra-loading" class="hidden">
          <div class="spinner"></div>
          <p class="label">Conducting the ensemble...</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Results Section -->
        <div id="orchestra-results" class="hidden">
          <div class="results-header">
            <h2 class="results-title">Synthesis Report</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="synthesis-section">
            <h3 class="label">Orchestrated Synthesis</h3>
            <div id="synthesis-text" class="prose"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="contributions-section">
            <h3 class="label">Model Contributions</h3>
            <div id="contributions-list" class="contributions-grid"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="conductor-note-section">
            <h3 class="label">Conductor's Note</h3>
            <div id="conductor-note" class="prose"></div>
          </div>

          <button id="new-question-btn" class="btn">Ask Another Question</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .orchestra-page { padding: var(--space-24) 0; }
  .page-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-16); max-width: 64ch; }
  .page-label { color: var(--ember); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .page-title { font-size: var(--text-5xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .page-desc { font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }

  .orchestra-interface {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-mid);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .input-section { margin-bottom: var(--space-12); }
  .input-wrapper { margin-bottom: var(--space-12); }
  .input-wrapper .label { display: block; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); color: var(--ember); }

  .orchestra-textarea {
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--surface-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    min-height: 150px;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .models-legend { padding: var(--space-8); background: var(--surface-3); border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--border-dim); }
  .models-legend .label { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); color: var(--text-primary); }

  .models-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(120px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-3); }
  .model-card {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    padding: var(--space-3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .model-name { display: block; color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
  .model-role { display: block; color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 0.75rem; }

  #orchestra-loading { text-align: center; padding: var(--space-20) 0; }
  .spinner {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border: 4px solid var(--ember-dim);
    border-top-color: var(--ember);
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-6);
  }
  @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  .results-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-12); }
  .results-title { font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--pale-gold); }

  .synthesis-section,
  .contributions-section,
  .conductor-note-section { margin-bottom: var(--space-12); }

  .synthesis-section .label,
  .contributions-section .label,
  .conductor-note-section .label { color: var(--ember); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }

  .contributions-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-6); }
  .contribution-card {
    background: var(--surface-3);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ember);
  }
  .contribution-model { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .contribution-role { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .contribution-insight { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

  .hidden { display: none !important; }

  /* Substrate Signature Taxonomy */
  .substrate-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .substrate-heading {
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .substrate-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .substrate-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    transition: border-color var(--duration-mid) var(--ease-out);
  }

  .substrate-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-bright);
  }

  .substrate-card--conductor {
    border-color: var(--ember-dim);
  }

  .substrate-card__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .substrate-card__symbol {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--ember);
    min-width: 2rem;
  }

  .substrate-card__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    flex: 1;
  }

  .substrate-card__model {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
  }

  .substrate-card__desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* Routing Principle */
  .routing-principle {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-10);
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ember);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .routing-principle__heading {
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .routing-principle__body {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    max-width: 80ch;
  }

  /* Five-Axis Routing */
  .routing-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    padding: var(--space-10);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-mid);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .routing-heading {
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .routing-axes {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .routing-axis {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .routing-axis__number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--ember);
    min-width: 2rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .routing-axis__content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
  }

  .routing-axis__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .routing-axis__desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
</style>

<script>
  const inputSection = document.getElementById('orchestra-input') as HTMLElement;
  const loading = document.getElementById('orchestra-loading') as HTMLElement;
  const results = document.getElementById('orchestra-results') as HTMLElement;
  const conductBtn = document.getElementById('conduct-btn') as HTMLElement;
  const newQuestionBtn = document.getElementById('new-question-btn') as HTMLElement;

  async function conductOrchestra() {
    const question = (document.getElementById('orchestra-question') as HTMLTextAreaElement).value;
    
    if (!question.trim()) {
      alert('Please ask a governance question.');
      return;
    }

    inputSection.classList.add('hidden');
    loading.classList.remove('hidden');

    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/orchestra', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ question }),
      });

      const report = await res.json();

      // Populate results
      (document.getElementById('synthesis-text') as HTMLElement).innerHTML = report.synthesis.replace(/\n/g, '<br>');
      (document.getElementById('conductor-note') as HTMLElement).innerHTML = report.conductorNote.replace(/\n/g, '<br>');

      const contributionsList = document.getElementById('contributions-list') as HTMLElement;
      contributionsList.innerHTML = report.modelContributions
        .map((c: any) => `
          <div class="contribution-card">
            <div class="contribution-model">${c.model}</div>
            <div class="contribution-role">${c.role}</div>
            <div class="contribution-insight">${c.insight}</div>
          </div>
        `)
        .join('');

      loading.classList.add('hidden');
      results.classList.remove('hidden');
    } catch (err) {
      alert('Orchestration failed. Please try again.');
      loading.classList.add('hidden');
      inputSection.classList.remove('hidden');
    }
  }

  conductBtn?.addEventListener('click', conductOrchestra);
  newQuestionBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    results.classList.add('hidden');
    inputSection.classList.remove('hidden');
    (document.getElementById('orchestra-question') as HTMLTextAreaElement).value = '';
  });
</script>
